title: Google\Cloud\GkeMultiCloud\V1\AzureNodePool
name: AzureNodePool
description:
An Anthos node pool running on Azure.

Generated from protobuf message google.cloud.gkemulticloud.v1.AzureNodePool

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

methods.name: __construct
methods.description: Constructor.

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: The name of this resource. Node pool names are formatted as projects/<project-number>/locations/<region>/azureClusters/<cluster-id>/azureNodePools/<node-pool-id>. For more details on Google Cloud resource names, see Resource Names

params.name: data.version
params.description: Required. The Kubernetes version (e.g. 1.19.10-gke.1000) running on this node pool.

params.name: data.config
params.description: Required. The node configuration of the node pool.

params.name: data.subnet_id
params.description: Required. The ARM ID of the subnet where the node pool VMs run. Make sure it's a subnet under the virtual network in the cluster configuration.

params.name: data.autoscaling
params.description: Required. Autoscaler configuration for this node pool.

params.name: data.state
params.description: Output only. The current state of the node pool.

params.name: data.uid
params.description: Output only. A globally unique identifier for the node pool.

params.name: data.reconciling
params.description: Output only. If set, there are currently pending changes to the node pool.

params.name: data.create_time
params.description: Output only. The time at which this node pool was created.

params.name: data.update_time
params.description: Output only. The time at which this node pool was last updated.

params.name: data.etag
params.description: Allows clients to perform consistent read-modify-writes through optimistic concurrency control. Can be sent on update and delete requests to ensure the client has an up-to-date value before proceeding.

params.name: data.annotations
params.description: Optional. Annotations on the node pool. This field has the same restrictions as Kubernetes annotations. The total size of all keys and values combined is limited to 256k. Keys can have 2 segments: prefix (optional) and name (required), separated by a slash (/). Prefix must be a DNS subdomain. Name must be 63 characters or less, begin and end with alphanumerics, with dashes (-), underscores (_), dots (.), and alphanumerics between.

params.name: data.max_pods_constraint
params.description: Required. The constraint on the maximum number of pods that can be run simultaneously on a node in the node pool.

params.name: data.azure_availability_zone
params.description: Optional. The Azure availability zone of the nodes in this nodepool. When unspecified, it defaults to 1.
